'''Domthok Monastery''' is a Buddhist monastery in [[Yushu County]], Qinghai, China. It is 60&nbsp;km southeast of Gyêgu on the western bank of the Dri Chu ([[Yangtze River]]) at 32.62924, 97.53449. A footbridge crosses the river here. The monastery is affiliated with [[Dzongsar Monastery]], south of [[Derge]], in [[Garze County]], [[Sichuan]].

There are two shops, a [[general store]] run by the monks and close by another selling Tibetan medicines. Petrol can be purchased in the yard adjacent to the newly built (2011) hostel. A small Tibetan village surrounds the [[monastery]].

